{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"padding","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"edges","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge","text":"Edge","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"text":"Set","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4EdgeO3SetV","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set"},{"text":" = .all, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"length","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGFloat","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:14CoreFoundation7CGFloatV"},{"text":"? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The set of edges to pad for this view. The default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set\/all","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"edges"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An amount, given in points, to pad this view on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified edges. If you set the value to "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", OpenSwiftUI uses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a platform-specific default amount. The default value of this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parameter is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"length"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that’s padded by the specified amount on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified edges.","type":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this modifier to add a specified amount of padding to one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"edges of the view. Indicate the edges to pad by naming either a single"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value from "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Edge\/Set"},{"type":"text","text":", or by specifying an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/Swift\/OptionSet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contains edge values:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text padded by 20 points on the bottom and trailing edges.\")","        .padding([.bottom, .trailing], 20)","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The order in which you apply modifiers matters. The example above","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applies the padding before applying the border to ensure that the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"border encompasses the padded region:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can omit either or both of the parameters. If you omit the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"length"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI uses a default amount of padding. If you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"omit the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"edges"},{"type":"text","text":", OpenSwiftUI applies the padding to all edges. Omit both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to add a default padding all the way around a view. OpenSwiftUI chooses a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default amount of padding that’s appropriate for the platform and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the presentation context."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["VStack {","    Text(\"Text with default padding.\")","        .padding()","        .border(.gray)","    Text(\"Unpadded text for comparison.\")","        .border(.yellow)","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above looks like this in iOS under typical conditions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To control the amount of padding independently for each edge, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"View\/padding(_:)-6pgqq","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". To pad all outside edges of a view by a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified amount, use "},{"code":"View\/padding(_:)-68shk","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Adds an equal padding amount to specific edges of this view."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/strokeshapeview\/padding(_:_:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Meth